body:
In development mode,  I'm seeing a hang when the view is missing.

For example,

  get('/', function() {
    this.render('index.ejs.html', {
      locals: {
        title: "hello"
      }
    })
  })

When the layout.ejs.html file is missing.  It hangs the response...

```
get('/public/*', function(path){
   // ...
})
```

This would match:
    /public/style.css
    /public/javascripts/app.js

etc

```
get('/user/:id/:op', function(id, op){

})
```

This could allow "page.haml" to utilize the haml
engine by default, while still assigning contentType to "html".
The API could perhaps look like:
    require('express/plugins/views').map['haml'] = { engine: 'haml', contentType: 'html' }

which could then supply some defaults such as sass, and haml.
Also at the user level this would be nice:
    use(View, { map: {
      whatever: { engine: 'haml', contentType: 'html' }
    }})

With a bit of closure magic we should be able to provide utility functions
to routes without this. Also now we may consider:

```
get('/user/:id/:operation', function(id, operation){

})
```
